Access logs are useful for user actions and failed requests.

document_id, user_id, and timestamp are the main correlation fields.

Access logs are stored in daily indices such as cmws-access-logs-%{+yyyy.MM.dd}.

The final normalized event data is stored in a unified process index such as cmws-process-events.


